members.name: FCVAR_PROTECTED
members.description:
Makes the ConVar value hidden from all clients (for example sv_password).
Reported as "prot" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_SPONLY
members.description:
Executing the command or changing the ConVar is only allowed in singleplayer.
Reported as "sp" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_ARCHIVE
members.description:
Save the ConVar value into config.cfg.
Reported as "a" by cvarlist, except Lua ConVars.

members.name: FCVAR_NOTIFY
members.description:
For serverside ConVars, notifies all players with blue chat text when the value gets changed.
Reported as "nf" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_USERINFO
members.description:
For clientside commands, sends the value to the server.
Reported as "user" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_UNLOGGED
members.description:
Don't log the ConVar changes to console/log files/users.
Reported as "log" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_REPLICATED
members.description:
For serverside ConVars, it will send its value to all clients. The ConVar with the same name must also exist on the client!
Reported as "rep" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_CHEAT
members.description:
Requires sv_cheats to be enabled to change the ConVar or run the command.
Reported as "cheat" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_DEMO
members.description:
Force the ConVar to be recorded by demo recordings.
Reported as "demo" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_DONTRECORD
members.description:
Opposite of FCVAR_DEMO, ensures the ConVar is not recorded in demos.
Reported as "norecord" by cvarlist.

members.name: FCVAR_NOT_CONNECTED
members.description: Makes the ConVar not changeable while connected to a server or in singleplayer.

members.name: DOTA_DEFAULT_MAX_TEAM
members.description: Default number of players per team.

members.name: DOTA_DEFAULT_MAX_TEAM_PLAYERS
members.description: Default number of non-spectator players supported.

members.name: DOTA_MAX_PLAYER_TEAMS
members.description: Max number of player teams supported.

members.name: DOTA_MAX_SPECTATOR_LOBBY_SIZE
members.description: Max number of viewers in a spectator lobby.

members.name: DOTA_MAX_TEAM
members.description: Max number of players per team.

members.name: DOTA_MAX_TEAM_PLAYERS
members.description: Max number of non-spectator players supported.

members.name: DOTA_MAX_PLAYERS
members.description: Max number of players connected to the server including spectators.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_MP_RESTORE_AMPLIFY_PERCENTAGE
members.description:
Total amplify value is clamped to 0.

Method Name: `GetModifierMPRestoreAmplify_Percentage`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_INCOMING_PHYSICAL_DAMAGE_CONSTANT
members.description:
This property controls 'physical' shield, if defined both on client and server. Return value on client should be current shield health, as a positive integer, on server - amount of damage blocked.

Method Name: `GetModifierIncomingPhysicalDamageConstant`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_INCOMING_SPELL_DAMAGE_CONSTANT
members.description:
This property controls 'spell' shield, if defined both on client and server. Return value on client should be current shield health, as a positive integer, on server - amount of damage blocked.

Method Name: `GetModifierIncomingSpellDamageConstant`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_PHYSICAL_ARMOR_BASE_PERCENTAGE
members.description:
Values above 100% are ignored.

Method Name: `GetModifierPhysicalArmorBase_Percentage`.

members.name: MODIFIER_EVENT_ON_ATTACK_ALLIED
members.description:
Happens even if attack can't be issued.

Method Name: `OnAttackAllied`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_IS_SCEPTER
members.description:
Applies scepter when this property is active

Method Name: `GetModifierScepter`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_IS_SHARD
members.description:
Applies shard when this property is active

Method Name: `GetModifierShard`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_HEALTHBAR_PIPS
members.description:
Return value is a count of pips.

Method Name: `GetModifierHealthBarPips`.

members.name: MODIFIER_PROPERTY_INCOMING_DAMAGE_CONSTANT
members.description:
This property controls 'universal' shield, if defined both on client and server. Return value on client should be current shield health, as a positive integer, on server - amount of damage blocked.

Method Name: `GetModifierIncomingDamageConstant`.

members.name: DMG_CRUSH
members.description: Caused by physics interaction. Ignored by airboat drivers.

members.name: DMG_SLASH
members.description: Sharp objects, such as Manhacks or other NPCs attacks.

members.name: DMG_VEHICLE
members.description: Hit by a vehicle. This will need to be set for passengers of some vehicle to receive damage.

members.name: DMG_BLAST
members.description: Explosion damage. Will be ignored by most vehicle passengers.

members.name: DMG_SHOCK
members.description: Electrical damage, shows smoke at the damage position.

members.name: DMG_SONIC
members.description: Sonic damage,used by the Gargantua and Houndeye NPCs.

members.name: DMG_NEVERGIB
members.description: Never creates gibs. Used by the crossbow.

members.name: DMG_RADIATION
members.description: Radiation. Will be ignored by most vehicle passengers.

members.name: DMG_DROWNRECOVER
members.description: Damage applied to the player to restore health after drowning.

members.name: DMG_REMOVENORAGDOLL
members.description: Don't create a ragdoll on death.
